    <div class="story-card__description">
                        <a class="story-card__series" href="https://www.propublica.org/series/state-of-disrepair">State of Disrepair</a>
        
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/idaho-resolution-would-lower-voting-threshold-to-pass-school-bonds">
                                    Idaho Resolution Would Aim to Lower Voting Threshold to Pass School Bonds
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Under restrictive school funding policies, Idaho districts struggle to repair and replace deteriorating buildings. If voters agree, the proposal would, in some elections, reduce the two-thirds threshold needed to pass bonds for school repairs.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <span class="name">Becca Savransky</span>, <a href="https://www.idahostatesman.com/">Idaho Statesman</a>, and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/asia-fields">Asia Fields</a>, ProPublica,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-02-22EST13:10">Feb. 22, 1:10 p.m. EST</time>
        </p>

                <p class="story-card__unit">Local Reporting Network</p>
            </div>
</div>
                    


        
                    
<div class="story-card story-card--standard">
    
    

                    
                    
    
        <div class="lead-art">
            <a class="aspect-3-2" href="https://www.propublica.org/article/state-active-shooter-training-schools-law-enforcement">
